    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1419" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀρήιος, ἄρειος</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἄρης</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">martial, warlike;</span> of
          men, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Μενέλᾱος, Αἴᾱς, υἶες Ἀχαιῶν</span>,
          etc.; also of weapons and armor (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τεύχεα,
            ἔντεα</span>); <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τεῖχος ἄρειον</span>,
          ‘martial’ wall, <i><span class="en">Il. 4.407</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.736</span></i>. 
        </div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
